<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.52/340: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-05T16:00:00+01:00">February 5, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 6—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>402. See my 389, February 4. Under Secretary Foreign Affairs assures
                                me instructions have been issued to Ministry Industry and Commerce
                                and other interested agencies to immediately suspend all exports of
                                wolfram to any destination pending preparation of counter proposals
                                to our request for wolfram embargo. Although he stated he is not in
                                a position to divulge nature of these counter proposals he has the
                                impression they include an agreement on the part of the Spanish
                                Government to limit exports to Germany to a quantity not exceeding
                                exports during 1943.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>